Lexical substitution data set for German
and GermEval 2015: LexSub shared task results
=============================================


Contents
--------

This archive contains the complete German lexical substitution data
set by Kostadin Cholakov et al., which was used for the GermEval 2015:
LexSub shared task at GSCL 2015.  The archive also contains the system
output and scoring software used in the task.  The files are grouped
into the following subdirectories:

dataset - The complete data set, split into "test" and "train" subsets.
          The data set is described in the paper by Cholakov et al. (see
	  below).

output  - Output for all baselines and systems at GermEval 2015: LexSub.
          These are described in the paper by Miller et al. (see below).

scorer  - Scoring software for calculating the "best", "OOT", and "GAP"
          metrics.  Documentation is provided in the subdirectory.


Licence
-------

The data set, which is derived from text from the German edition of
Wikipedia <https://de.wikipedia.org/>, is licensed under the Creative
Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported licence
<https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/>.

The scoring programs are governed by their own licences as described
in the source code.


Citation
--------

To reference the data set and system output, please use the following
citations:

Kostadin Cholakov, Chris Biemann, Judith Eckle-Kohler, and Iryna
Gurevych. Lexical Substitution Dataset for German. In: Proceedings of
the 9th International Conference on Language Resources and Evaluation
(LREC 2014), pages 1406-1411, May 2014.
<http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/545_Paper.pdf>

Tristan Miller, Darina Benikova, and Sallam Abualhaija. GermEval 2015:
LexSub -- A Shared Task for German-language Lexical Substitution.  In:
Proceedings of GermEval 2015: LexSub, pages 1-9, September 2015.
<https://sites.google.com/site/germeval2015/program/2015_GermEval_LexSub.pdf?attredirects=0&d=1>



Tristan Miller
28 September 2015
